&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Staff Nurse, Band 5, Outwood&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us in making a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Surrey and Sussex, our dedicated paediatric unit comprises of a 30-bedded ward, which includes a dedicated day surgery area, shared care oncology cubicles and High Dependency beds. We also have a Child Assessment Unit, which accepts children from a variety of sources, for acute assessment and treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and motivated paediatric nurse to work as part of our busy Paediatric team across the unit. Working together, you will be passionate and committed to innovative practice, in an environment where children and their families are the focus of attention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education and training is important to us and we fully support and promote the development of our Paediatric team. You will have the opportunity to develop skills, experience and knowledge across the unit and will receive support in your role from our dedicated team of children’s nurses, and Paediatric Clinical Educator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Ellen Parker, Unit Manager (ellenparker1@nhs.net / 01737 768511 ext 6415)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 13/11/2020 (midnight)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
